 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udjalinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Djalinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/29/01 1:40:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade hotkeys</span><hr size=1> I still don't understand why anyone would want evade on a macro.<br>
<br>
It takes only the most minimal of coordination to hit &quot;attack off/hide/attack on&quot; and it wastes a hotkey slot on top of that.  You only have 10 slots, and two of them should already be &quot;hide&quot; and &quot;sneak&quot;, just make sure &quot;hide&quot; is right next to whatever your &quot;attack&quot; key is mapped to.<br>
<br>
By putting evade onto a macro, you sacrifice the ability to see when hide is refreshed.  You also can't stop attacking and wait for just the right moment to hide in between hits, if you were so unfortunate as to attract a beat down.  If you fail evade on your little macro, you start attacking all over again automatically, hooray for more aggro!  If you're fighting something that can kill you in about 5 seconds should it turn on you, trusting your aggro management to a macro is unwise, not to mention annoying to everyone around you when the tank loses aggro while you die.<br>
<br>
