<i>Twisted Dreams</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udjalinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Djalinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/29/01 4:29:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade hotkeys</span><hr size=1> Nonsense?  That's a little harsh, especially since the original poster just proved one of by points by stating that he has his normal &quot;Hide&quot; key on page 2.<br>
<br>
I suppose what I was trying to get across with all those silly examples is that aggro management is more than just having evade go off every 10 seconds and hoping for the best.  By entrusting evade to a macro, you're losing a degree of control.  The more direct control you have over your aggro management, the better chance you have of surviving.<br>
<br>
